\f6\b \cf0 Q:
\f1\b0  When I check the page in the 
\f5\i \'d2Code\'d3
\f1\i0  view in RapidWeaver I see warnings about empty 
\f3\fs24 <span>\'c9</span> 
\f1\fs26 tags. Why does this happen?
\f6\b \
A:
\f1\b0  This happens when you are using source-highlight v2.x and have deselected the option 
\f5\i \'d2Apply inline color CSS\'d3
\f1\i0 . The reason is that source-highlight v2.x with default definitions creates a 
\f3\fs24 <span>\'c9</span>
\f1\fs26  tag around whitespace when it converts the text to HTML. This does not happen with source-highlight v.1.11 so this is a regression in version 2.x. For that reason I have decided, at least for now, to leave this without adding a \'d2workaround\'d3 for it in High-Light. This may change in the future.\

